</li>
<li id="cite_note-2"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">C.D.C. Reeve, <i>Plato on Love:</i> Lysis, Symposium, Phaedrus, Alcibiades <i>with Selections from</i> Republic<i> and</i> Laws (Hackett, 2006), p. xxi <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=E1lQNf2EfEUC&amp;pg=PP25">online</a>; Martti Nissinen, <i>Homoeroticism in the Biblical World: A Historical Perspective</i>, translated by Kirsi Stjerna (Augsburg Fortress, 1998, 2004), p. 57 <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=-sHSNPG85tUC&amp;pg=PA57">online</a>; Nigel Blake <i>et al.</i>, <i>Education in an Age of Nihilism</i> (Routledge, 2000), p. 183 <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=lgkOAAAAQAAJ&amp;pg=PA183">online.</a></span>
