<li id="cite_note-11"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">See Osborne following. Gloria Ferrari, however, notes that there were conventions of age pertaining to sexual activity, and if a man violated these by seducing a boy who was too young to consent to becoming an <i>eromenos</i>, the <a href="/wiki/Sexual_predator" title="Sexual predator">predator</a> might be subject to prosecution under the law of <i><a href="/wiki/Hubris" title="Hubris">hubris</a></i>; <i>Figures of Speech: Men and Maidens in Ancient Greece</i> (University of Chicago Press, 2002), pp. 139–140.</span>
